oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cragfont dining room
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: First floor room located in the north wing of Cragfont. Furnished as a dining room, showing dining table, fireplace, and mirror above mantel. Another room is visible through the open door. The walls have wainscot panels on the lower half.

The late Georgian style home was built between 1798 and 1802, and was originally home of General James Winchester. It was named after the Rocky Bluff it is located on. Cragfont was occupied by the Winchester family until 1864.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Boucher, Jack E.
